name: PageReference
description: A PageReference is a reference to an instantiation of a page. Among other attributes, PageReferences consist of a URL and a set of query parameter names and values.

forresource(string,string).name: forResource
forresource(string,string).signature: public static System.PageReference forResource(String resourceName, String path)
forresource(string,string).overrideSignature: public static override System.PageReference forResource(String resourceName, String path)
forresource(string,string).description: Generate a new instance of the PageReference class for the specified sObject record.

forresource(string).name: forResource
forresource(string).overrideSignature: public static override System.PageReference forResource(String resourceName)
forresource(string).description: Create a PageReference for a static resource, by name.

getanchor().name: getAnchor
getanchor().description: Returns the name of the anchor referenced in the page’s URL. That is, the part of the URL after the hashtag (#).

getcontent().name: getContent
getcontent().description: Returns the output of the page, as displayed to a user in a web browser.

getcontentaspdf().name: getContentAsPDF
getcontentaspdf().description: Returns the page in PDF, regardless of the <apex:page> component’s renderAs attribute.

getcookies().name: getCookies
getcookies().description: Returns a map of cookie names and cookie objects, where the key is a String of the cookie name and the the value contains the cookie object with that name.

getheaders().name: getHeaders
getheaders().description: Returns a map of the request headers, where the key string contains the name of the header, and the value string contains the value of the header.

getparameters().name: getParameters
getparameters().description: Returns a map of the query string parameters for the PageReference; both POST and GET parameters are included. The key string contains the name of the parameter, while the value string contains the value of the parameter.

getredirect().name: getRedirect
getredirect().description: Returns the current value of the PageReference object's redirect attribute.

geturl().name: getUrl
geturl().description: Returns the relative URL associated with the PageReference when it was originally defined, including any query string parameters and anchors.

setanchor(string).name: setAnchor
setanchor(string).description: Create a PageReference for a static resource, by name.

setcookies(cookie[]).name: setCookies
setcookies(cookie[]).description: Creates a list of cookie objects. Used in conjunction with the Cookie class.

setredirect(boolean).name: setRedirect
setredirect(boolean).description: Sets the value of the PageReference object's redirect attribute. If set to true, a redirect is performed through a client side redirect.

pagereference(string).name: PageReference
pagereference(string).description: Creates a new instance of the PageReference class using the specified URL.

partialurl.name: partialURL
partialurl.description: The partial URL of a page hosted on the Lightning platform or a full external URL.

pagereference(sobject).name: PageReference
pagereference(sobject).description: Generate a new instance of the PageReference class for the specified sObject record.

record.name: record
record.description: The sObject record that references the ApexPage. The reference must be an ApexPage.
